    "analysis": "We scanned metric.csv and computed global P95 per (cmdb_id, kpi_name) and then inspected the incident window (2020-05-23 04:30–05:00 Asia/Shanghai). The compact top-20 results show many DB service KPIs with full-window anomalies: multiple db_* components have 'Hang' == 1, 'On_Off_State' == 1, and other DB KPIs (MEM_Total, Row_Lock, SctRead_Per_Sec) with anomaly_count equal to nearly all points in the window. Earliest anomalies for these top series are at 2020-05-23 04:30:00 CST (Asia/Shanghai). Overall, 2,047 distinct (cmdb_id,kpi_name) series were scanned and 1,808 of them had at least one point in the window exceeding their global P95. This strongly suggests a widespread DB-level problem starting at 04:30, but multiple db_* services are affected. To localize the root cause component and reason we must use traces to find which service/container is the downstream faulty one in call chains and whether trace-level latency or failure metrics correlate with the DB anomalies. Next step: analyze trace.csv by computing global thresholds per (cmdb_id, trace_name) using the full trace series, then inspect the incident window and produce compact aggregates (anomaly counts, earliest anomaly timestamps, max values) to identify which traces and components show abnormal behavior in the incident window.",
