    "instruction": "Using trace.csv do the following and return compact aggregates (limit to top 20 rows):\n1) For each unique pair (cmdb_id, trace_name) compute the global P95 using all rows in trace.csv (store full table in kernel memory but do not print it).\n2) Filter trace.csv to the incident window: 2020-05-23 04:30:00 to 2020-05-23 05:00:00 Asia/Shanghai.\n3) For each (cmdb_id, trace_name) produce: cmdb_id, trace_name, global_p95, window_point_count, anomaly_count (value >= global_p95), earliest_anomaly_timestamp_in_window (Asia/Shanghai; NULL if none), max_value_in_window (NULL if no points).\n4) Return the top 20 rows sorted by anomaly_count descending then earliest_anomaly_timestamp_in_window ascending, and also return two counts: total number of distinct (cmdb_id,trace_name) series scanned and how many had anomaly_count>0. Keep outputs compact and only include the specified columns and counts."
